      • verifyRequestMoneyCases_topupLimitReached_viaMobile

        public void verifyRequestMoneyCases_topupLimitReached_viaMobile()
                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        method to verify the different send money scenarios. Below are the covered scenarios for now: 1) Top up Limit Reached - Trying to request money which exceeds the 10000 limit.(mobile/contact list/email) 2) invalid amount case - less than Rs. 5 (mobile/contact list/email) 3) empty transfer attempt - trying to send Rs. 0 (mobile/contact list/email) 4) successful attempt - money sent successfully 5) Invalid Mobile/Email 6) Requesting Money to Self(mobile/email) 7) Requesting Money when logged out (mobile/contact list/email) 8) Non-exisiting Mobile/Email 9) A requesting money B Accepting (mobile/contact list/email) 10) A requesting B Declines (mobile/contact list/email) 11) A requests and cancels (mobile/contact list/email)
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - - When any exception comes
